The paper deals with the problem of minimizing transmit power in multi-user communication, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of user selection algorithms also suggests a possible category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions beamforming vectors and power allocation scalars, which are common in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the study of performance comparison between different user selection algorithms could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
